            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>In this correspondence, Alfred Bloxham, a miller at Nashville, Ill., wrote to members of his family about financial, health, and family matters. The collection also contains a letter, dated Jun 22, 1841, from H. H. Rasin of St. Louis, Mo., certifying Bloxham as a skilled miller.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


